basicPropertyValues.val: Current Procedural Terminology\, more commonly known as CPT®\, refers to a medical code set created and maintained by the American Medical Association — and used by physicians\, allied health professionals\, nonphysician practitioners\, hospitals\, outpatient facilities\, and laboratories to represent the services and procedures they perform. No provider of outpatient services gets paid without reporting the proper CPT® codes. \[Description taken from this site\]\(https\://www.aapc.com/codes/cpt-codes-range/\)\]
